# What to include

Use these section headings exactly. Omit a section only if it is truly empty. Prefer bullets under each heading.

## Purpose
Objective or question being pursued on this branch. Include the specific user ask or quoted wording when it materially shaped the branch.

## User intent & branch delta
What the user was trying to learn, change, or prove in this branch; what changed relative to the shared ancestor; and which asks remain relevant outside this branch.

## Outcome
Concrete results, findings, and insights worth carrying forward.

## Constraints & preferences
Requirements, preferences, or constraints that shaped the work on this branch.

## Key decisions
Decisions made with brief rationale, including approaches tried, disproven, or ruled out.

## Status
What is done, what is in progress, what remains unverified, what is unresolved or blocked, and what should not be retried without new evidence. Distinguish observed facts from inferences.

## Next steps
Concrete actions for continuing this work, in order. Note dependencies between steps.

## Mandatory reading
Exact file paths relevant to this branch's work.

# Style
- Keep the summary concise and continuation-friendly
- Preserve exact file paths, symbol names, commands, error text, and user wording where useful
- Make it obvious what is reusable versus branch-local
- If a files-touched or user-message block is present, use it as authoritative context but do not repeat it exhaustively
- Output only markdown for the summary